      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. So if the stagnation pressure is higher because the air is being brought to a stop, what specifically happens to the airspeed reading if there's a partial blockage in the pitot tube itself, versus a blockage in the static port? Can you explain the direction of the error in those two cases?",
      "source": "evaluator"
